    "description": "Kaneko Seeds Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, production and sale agricultural seeds in Japan. It operates through Seeds and Seedlings Business, Flower Business, Agricultural Materials Business, and Facility Materials Business segments. The company offers bulbs, and flower and horticultural supplies; vegetable and pasture seeds, virus-free seedlings, and seed potatoes; grass, forage crop, green manure crop, landscaping, and turfgrass seeds; and greenhouses and agricultural production materials. It also sells flower seedlings and vegetable seeds; young tomatoes and carnations; pesticides and coated fertilizers; and agricultural chemicals, resin materials, and hydroponic cultivation systems. In addition, the company engages in the sale and repair of greenhouse horticulture equipment; design, construct, and sale of hydroponic cultivation plants; and landscaping and slope construction contracting work. It serves home gardening enthusiasts and commercial growers; and home centers, gardening specialty stores, and gardening wholesalers. Kaneko Seeds Co., Ltd. was founded in 1895 and is headquartered in Maebashi, Japan."
